When defining "activities relating to Petroleum production and development" for the purposes of the quarterly report, a Petroleum Exploration Reporting Entity or Petroleum Production Reporting Entity should:

* Ensure that the activities are directly related to the production and development of petroleum resources, as per Rule 12.13.1(b) and Rule 12.13.3(a);
* Confirm that any forecast commodity prices used in the quarterly report were arrived at on reasonable grounds, as per Rule 11.8.3(2);
* Consider all relevant risks and uncertainties associated with the activities, including but not limited to, operational, financial, and geological risks;
* Ensure that the activities are conducted in accordance with applicable laws, regulations, and industry standards;
* Disclose any material changes or updates to the activities, including changes to production targets, forecasts, or development plans;
* Provide a clear and transparent description of the activities, including the location, type, and scope of the activities;
* Ensure that the activities are properly accounted for and disclosed in the quarterly report, including any relevant financial information;
* Consider the guidance provided by international standard-setting bodies, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), in relation to anti-money laundering and combating the financing of terrorism (AML/CFT) risks associated with the activities;
* Ensure that the activities are subject to regular internal audits and assessments to ensure compliance with regulatory obligations and industry standards;
* Consider the guidance provided by the Regulator and relevant Rulebooks in relation to the preparation and disclosure of the quarterly report.

By following these requirements and procedures, a Petroleum Exploration Reporting Entity or Petroleum Production Reporting Entity can ensure that its quarterly report provides a comprehensive and accurate picture of its activities relating to Petroleum production and development.

