In addition to these changes, other triggers for updated CDD measures may include:

* Any Transactions that are not reasonably consistent with the Relevant Person's knowledge of the customer (rule 8.1.2(b));
* Any change in the purpose or intended nature of the Relevant Person's relationship with the customer (rule 8.1.2(c));
* Any other matter that might affect the Relevant Person's risk assessment of the customer (rule 8.1.2(d)).

